From Perry Metzger Subject Re Screw the people crypto is for hard core hackers spooks only John F Carr writes Perry Metzger writes Well I'm not a lawyer but from what I can tell this is completely and utterly The does NOT have an official secrets We do have laws that will punish you for revealing what classified information you learned in your capacity as a government official contractor etc and we have laws that prohibit stealing such However if they sell you the chip I can't see that they can make reverse engineering it and revealing the details In most cases information you come by properly is yours to use as you wish but there are certainly If you write a paper which includes sufficiently detailed information on how to build a nuclear weapon it is As I understand the law nuclear weapons design is automatically classified even if you do the work I believe you are then not allowed to read your own Oh What about the precedent in which nuclear weapons information was published in The Progressive I was under the impression that the court held that prior restraint could NOT be Any lawyers out there Perry Metzger Laissez faire laissez Le monde va de lui